From: OnePlus Nord CE5 Kernel Workflow <kernel@local>
Date: 2026-06-08
Subject: [PATCH] mm/zram: fix broken hybrid_swap (RAM expansion) and zram on OnePlus mt6897 (OOS16)

OnePlus/Oppo ship a proprietary memory-compression stack
("hybridswap_zram") in the vendor tree
(vendor/oplus/kernel/mm/hybridswap_zram) which *replaces* the upstream
GKI zram driver. Its Kconfig declares:

    config HYBRIDSWAP_ZRAM
        depends on ... && !ZRAM

and the OnePlus GKI common tree consequently:
  1. comments out the upstream zram build in
     drivers/block/Makefile  ("# obj-$(CONFIG_ZRAM) += zram/"), and
  2. ships CONFIG_ZRAM=m in gki_defconfig (so the symbol exists for ABI
     but produces no usable /dev/zram device).

Community KernelSU/SUSFS builds (e.g. WildKernels) build ONLY the GKI
Image + modules from this common tree and never compile the vendor
hybridswap_zram module. Result on-device: no working zram block device
is registered, so both classic zram swap AND OnePlus "RAM expansion"
(RSM / hybrid swap, which layers a backing device on top of zram) are
dead -- mkswap/swapon on /dev/block/zram0 fail because the node never
appears.

This patch restores a self-contained, working zram by:
  - re-enabling the in-tree upstream zram driver build, and
  - building zram + zsmalloc + the compressors statically into the
    Image (=y) so a GKI-only build still gets /dev/zram0 without
    depending on the never-built vendor module, and enabling
    CONFIG_ZRAM_WRITEBACK so a backing device (the RAM-expansion file)
    can be attached via /sys/block/zram0/backing_dev.

Note: this is the GKI-side fix that makes zram and RAM-expansion work
on community kernels. It intentionally does NOT try to resurrect the
proprietary hybridswap container (CONFIG_HYBRIDSWAP*), which needs the
closed vendor module + userspace; upstream zram + writeback covers the
swap and RAM-expansion use cases.

---
--- a/drivers/block/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/block/Makefile
@@ -32,7 +32,7 @@
 obj-$(CONFIG_BLK_DEV_RBD)     += rbd.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_BLK_DEV_PCIESSD_MTIP32XX)	+= mtip32xx/
 
-# obj-$(CONFIG_ZRAM) += zram/
+obj-$(CONFIG_ZRAM) += zram/
 obj-$(CONFIG_BLK_DEV_RNBD)	+= rnbd/
 
 obj-$(CONFIG_BLK_DEV_NULL_BLK)	+= null_blk/
--- a/arch/arm64/configs/gki_defconfig
+++ b/arch/arm64/configs/gki_defconfig
@@ -323,7 +323,7 @@
 # CONFIG_ARM_SCPI_POWER_DOMAIN is not set
 # CONFIG_EFI_ARMSTUB_DTB_LOADER is not set
 CONFIG_GNSS=y
-CONFIG_ZRAM=m
+CONFIG_ZRAM=y
 CONFIG_BLK_DEV_LOOP=y
 CONFIG_BLK_DEV_LOOP_MIN_COUNT=16
 CONFIG_BLK_DEV_RAM=y
@@ -774,3 +774,12 @@
 CONFIG_KUNIT_DEBUGFS=y
 # CONFIG_KUNIT_DEFAULT_ENABLED is not set
 # CONFIG_RUNTIME_TESTING_MENU is not set
+CONFIG_SWAP=y
+CONFIG_ZSMALLOC=y
+CONFIG_ZSMALLOC_STAT=y
+CONFIG_ZRAM_DEF_COMP_LZORLE=y
+CONFIG_ZRAM_WRITEBACK=y
+CONFIG_CRYPTO_LZO=y
+CONFIG_CRYPTO_LZ4=y
+CONFIG_CRYPTO_LZ4HC=y
+CONFIG_CRYPTO_ZSTD=y
